definitions.definition: A machine consisting of a drum on an axle , a friction brake or ratchet and pawl , and a crank handle or prime mover (often an electric or hydraulic motor), with or without gearing , to give increased mechanical advantage when hoisting or hauling on a rope or cable .
A hoisting device used for loading or unloading cargo , or for pulling in lines .
A wince (machine used in dyeing or steeping cloth).
A kick , as of an animal, from impatience or uneasiness .
